There's a reason your ai coded landing page looks like a nuns ass!

(bland, attracts no viewers, and makes no conversions 😉)

ok... questionable hook aside...

i got fed up paying $200 for sh*tty webflow or framer templates so i made my own w/ @cursor_ai 

BUT... every time i used Ai to add a new feature or design it would overwrite something else and lose all my progress! 😡

So, If you keep BURNING through credits, getting WEIRD designs, and get CONSTANT hallucinations...

Buckle up, bookmark, like and share this bad boy & watch this full video

Turns out the fix is relatively simple, you're lazy...

Basically the issue you're having is Ai has a limited context window

If the feature youre working on is buried within 1,000+ lines of code, and your composer prompt is:

✍️ 50% explaining where to find the feature (ps. if ur not doing this already, thats not helping, so start)

✍️ 50% telling it how to update this feature

the ai can easily get lost, edit other features, or just forget what you asked it

The solution:

#1 STOP telling ai to "build me a modern sleek landing page blah blah blah". im bored, we're all bored, and you're lazy. We need to break this up

#2 Plan out your landing page layout and split it into sections, eg: Hero, Section 1 (demo), Section 2 (FAQ), Section 3 (Reviews) etc

#3 Tell Cursor / Windsurf to code new UI components and add them to the /app/Components folder (For NextJS)

#4 WORK on one component at a time and use the tagging method in this video to gradually improve designs of EACH component

BONUS: If you now want to move things around on your site just say "Swap the order (@)Component_1 and (@)Component_2 in the (@)Layout.js"

its so much faster

(if you've got this far and havent watched the video.... cmon m8)

The principle is IDENTICAL when building apps too, ill do some more vids on that soon

If ur confused.. rewatch this video

If ur still confused.. AMA in comments👇
